{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02618/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02618"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:26:18"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man compares dress fabrics on his model."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02618","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02618"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1/e433f33c-4872-4b04-b615-0a5944bb48ab","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:40:03.470Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>When draped on Alma’s shoulders, the fabric swatches evoke the epaulettes of military dress, suggesting that the dress itself serves an armorlike function.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:991.0094212651414,349.421265141319,329.47510094212646,186.0565275908479"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1/aede2ea0-41e1-4fe0-b560-e161bb224d4d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:40:15.951Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The light between them in this shot suggests that something is coming to the surface through this relationship.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:527.1601615074024,79.38088829071333,472.89367429340507,250.6594885598923"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1/294ad6f1-ee57-4279-83ad-275aa913fc49","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:40:34.485Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds rejects the blue fabric as “too serious” for Alma, opting instead for a light pink. He wants to emphasize her youth and separate her from what is heavy or difficult. At this point, he still views her presence as temporary and does not want her to participate in the serious parts of his life. Notably, Reynolds does not ask her what her opinion is, choosing for her what color, and through that what mood, her dress should convey.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02618/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:414.75100942126517,388.18304172274566,339.81157469717357,267.4562584118438"}}}]}]}]}